stylometry: Some of the advantages of simulation models is they allow you to see a distribution rather than just an answer (such as mean, minimum, maximum, standard deviation). Simulation models allow you to run multiple simulations (with multiple interations) at once, for multiple inputs. These types of models allow you to ask "what-if questions" without actually changing the entire system. Simulation models also allow you to see how sensitive the system is to change it. Someone may use a simulation model in a management or business situation when trying to decide how many servers a restaurant needs. When running the simulation, you could test out 8 servers, 10 servers, 12 servers, etc. all at once and compare their averages, min and max, standard deviation, etc. In business, simulation models help determine the best strategy a business could use.
